  <p class="text-starlight-200 leading-relaxed">
    I am a physicist with a deep curiosity about the fundamental laws of nature
    and the physics of the universe. My research focuses on the light-scattering
    properties of cosmic dust and their role in shaping the observable universe.
    I investigate how tiny dust particles, such as those found in comets, asteroids,
    and interstellar clouds, influence planetary systems and contribute to the
    evolution of life on Earth.
  </p>
